The credit line will provide much-needed liquidity for companies in infrastructure, energy and manufacturing particularly value-addition and are targeted at the youth in particular. KCB Group Chief Executive Officer and Managing Director, Joshua Oigara, said the partnership was part of the bank’s efforts towards helping achieve the economic transformation of Kenya in line with the government’s agenda. KCB is East Africa’s largest commercial bank which was established in 1896 in Kenya but has now spread its wings to Tanzania, South Sudan, Uganda, Rwanda, Burundi and Ethiopia. The AfDB is Africa’s premier development finance institution, with offices in 44 African countries.

--ANA--